evaluation.response:
If you're not eating enough for your body, even if you're not feeling hungry, it could be causing problems. 

If you make big changes to your eating and exercise habits without talking to anyone about your plan, it can be hard to make sure you're staying safe and staying on track. Maybe ask a parent to help you find a registered dietitian at your doctor's office, or a nutritionist if that's something available to you. They can help you come up with a plan that will be exactly what you need.

If you're interested in learning more about healthy eating, there are tons of free and low-cost resources available. Check out your doctor's office or the school counselor for more information.&#x20;

It is great that you are committed to trying to make positive changes in your life.&#x20;

Some people might eat safe foods, skip meals, and obsess over body image and exercise, any of these could be signs of behaviors that are common to many eating disorders. These health issues are not healthy or sustainable in the long run and can have serious effects on both physical and mental health.

Asking for help is a brave thing to do. Reach out to a parent, school counselor, coach, or dietician. They can help you develop a personal and positive relationship with improving your life.

The relationship between body image and progress on your goals might be justice viewed through the lenses of media and admiration that it's good to be thinner. Denying yourself the joy and nutrients of eating to be able to say the number on the scale is as low as possible is not something to admire. Is that really what's most important to you? Have you thought about all you enjoy doing it the same amount when the number on the scale is higher?

At one point you said you thought that losing weight would help with PE and mental health, but the changes you've been making might have the opposite effect.&#x20;

It is very helpful to be supported, stay positive, and have good examples as you are learning more about body image and weight and making improvements in your life.
